<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;">Strength</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="50%" style="border-right: 1px dotted #aaa;">5,600,000 Chinese<br />
700+ US aircraft<br />
over 5000 Soviet advisors and pilots</td>
<td width="50%" style="padding-left: 0.25em;">3,200,000 Japanese,<br />
900,000 Chinese collaborators<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><br /></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;">Casualties and losses</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="50%" style="border-right: 1px dotted #aaa;">3,220,000 military (including wounded, prisoners and missing),<br />
17,530,000 civilians<br />
227 Soviet dead<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
<td width="50%" style="padding-left: 0.25em;">Estimated at 1.8 million casualties with total Military deaths 943,259:<br />
388,605 Japanese military killed<br />
432,000 Chinese military collaborators killed<br />
30,304 Chinese collaborators from Taiwan<br />
14,527 Korean collaborators.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="font-size:90%; border-top: 1px solid #aaa;"><sup>1</sup> On July 1942, the <a href="/wiki/Flying_Tigers" title="Flying Tigers">Flying Tigers</a> became an official <a href="/wiki/14th_Air_Force" title="14th Air Force" class="mw-redirect">United States Army Air Force unit</a>.<br />
<sup>2</sup> Various Japanese <a href="/wiki/Puppet_state" title="Puppet state">puppet regimes</a> provided significant manpower to support the Japanese occupation.</td>
</tr>
