<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> China didn't declare a war on Japan <i>de jure</i> until December 1941, for fear of alienating the Western powers in Asia. Once Japan broadened the conflict, China was released of this binding, and was free to officially declare war on Japan.</li>
